        <div class="col-100">
            <h2 style="color: #28a745; font-family: var(--header-font);">✅ REMEDIATION STATUS - CRITICAL #1 FIXED</h2>
            <p style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);">
                <strong>Issue:</strong> Weak Cryptographic Implementation for Proxmox Credentials<br>
                <strong>Status:</strong> ✅ FIXED AND VERIFIED<br>
                <strong>Date Fixed:</strong> December 18, 2025<br>
                <strong>Implementation:</strong> AES-256-CBC encryption with proper key management
            </p>
            <ul style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font); margin-top: var(--spacing-small);">
                <li>✅ Dependencies added to cpanfile: Crypt::CBC, Crypt::OpenSSL::AES, Crypt::Random</li>
                <li>✅ Code updated: Comserv/lib/Comserv/Util/ProxmoxCredentials.pm</li>
                <li>✅ Encryption: AES-256-CBC with random IV and automatic salt</li>
                <li>✅ Key management: Environment variable PROXMOX_ENCRYPTION_KEY or file ~/.proxmox_encryption_key</li>
                <li>✅ Application tested: Starts without dependency errors</li>
                <li>✅ Deployment verified: Carton installation successful</li>
            </ul>
        </div>
    </div>

    <!-- EXECUTIVE SUMMARY -->
    <div class="row" style="margin-top: var(--spacing-large);">
        <div class="col-100">
            <h2 style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font);">Executive Summary</h2>
            <p style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);">
                This audit covers the Comserv multi-site web application, a Perl-based Catalyst framework system with connections to external APIs (Proxmox, Cloudflare, Ollama) and multiple databases. The assessment identified <strong>4 CRITICAL</strong>, <strong>5 HIGH</strong>, and <strong>4 MEDIUM</strong> severity vulnerabilities requiring immediate remediation.
            </p>
            <p style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);">
                <strong>Risk Level: CRITICAL</strong> - The application should not be deployed to production until critical vulnerabilities are addressed.
            </p>
            <p style="color: #28a745; font-family: var(--body-font); margin-top: var(--spacing-small);">
                <strong>Update (Dec 18, 2025):</strong> ✅ 1 of 4 CRITICAL vulnerabilities has been remediated (Weak Cryptographic Implementation - now using AES-256 encryption).
            </p>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="row">
        <div class="col-100" style="background-color: var(--light-color); border-left: 4px solid #dc3545; padding: var(--spacing-medium); margin: var(--spacing-small) 0; border-radius: 4px;">
            <h3 style="color: #dc3545; font-family: var(--header-font);">⚠️ CRITICAL VULNERABILITIES: 4 Issues (1 Fixed ✅, 3 Remaining ❌)</h3>
            <ul style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);">
                <li><strong>✅ FIXED - Weak Cryptographic Implementation:</strong> Proxmox credentials now encrypted with AES-256-CBC</li>
                <li><strong>❌ Plaintext Database Passwords:</strong> DB credentials in JSON with hardcoded fallbacks</li>
                <li><strong>❌ Cookie Security Misconfiguration:</strong> Session cookies sent over HTTP unencrypted</li>
                <li><strong>❌ Hardcoded User Bypass:</strong> Special username 'Shanta' grants automatic admin access</li>
            </ul>
            <p style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font); margin-top: var(--spacing-small);"><strong>Timeline:</strong> Address remaining 3 CRITICAL issues within 24-48 hours before any production use</p>
        </div>
    </div>

