    <div class="row" style="margin-top: var(--spacing-large);">
        <div class="col-100">
            <h2 id="critical-vulnerabilities" style="color: #dc3545; font-family: var(--header-font);">🔴 CRITICAL SEVERITY VULNERABILITIES</h2>
            <p style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);">These vulnerabilities must be fixed before any production deployment. Timeline: 24-48 hours.</p>
        </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Critical Issue 1: Weak Cryptography - FIXED -->
    <div class="row">
        <div class="col-100" style="background-color: #d4edda; border-left: 6px solid #28a745; padding: var(--spacing-medium); margin: var(--spacing-medium) 0; border-radius: 4px;">
            <h3 style="color: #28a745; font-family: var(--header-font);">✅ 1. Weak Cryptographic Implementation for Proxmox Credentials - FIXED</h3>
            
            <p style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);"><strong>File:</strong> <code>Comserv/lib/Comserv/Util/ProxmoxCredentials.pm</code> | <strong>CVSS:</strong> 9.1 | <strong>OWASP:</strong> A02:2021 | <strong>Status:</strong> ✅ RESOLVED</p>

            <h4 style="color: #28a745; font-family: var(--header-font);">🚨 Previous Problem (VULNERABLE)</h4>
            <ul style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);">
                <li><strong>SHA256 is NOT encryption:</strong> Previous code stored passwords in format <code>OBFS:hash:PASSWORD_HERE</code> - plaintext was visible</li>
                <li><strong>Hardcoded salt:</strong> Single static salt "ComservProxmoxSalt2025" - if source compromised, all passwords exposed</li>
                <li><strong>File system attack:</strong> Anyone with file access could read passwords directly</li>
                <li><strong>Git history exposure:</strong> All historical passwords in repository history</li>
            </ul>

            <h4 style="color: #28a745; font-family: var(--header-font);">✅ Current Solution (SECURE)</h4>
            <ul style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);">
                <li><strong>✅ AES-256-CBC encryption:</strong> Industry-standard encryption (not obfuscation)</li>
                <li><strong>✅ Random IV:</strong> randomiv => 1 ensures unique ciphertext for same plaintext</li>
                <li><strong>✅ Automatic salt:</strong> Built-in salt generation by Crypt::CBC</li>
                <li><strong>✅ Encrypted format:</strong> <code>ENC:[base64-encrypted-data]</code></li>
                <li><strong>✅ Key management:</strong> Environment variable PROXMOX_ENCRYPTION_KEY or file ~/.proxmox_encryption_key (chmod 0600)</li>
                <li><strong>✅ Legacy data support:</strong> Automatic detection and handling of plaintext credentials (graceful migration)</li>
            </ul>

            <h4 style="color: #28a745; font-family: var(--header-font);">✅ Implementation Code</h4>
            <div style="background-color: white; padding: var(--spacing-small); border: 1px solid var(--border-color); margin: var(--spacing-small) 0; border-radius: 4px;">
                <pre style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: monospace; background-color: #f5f5f5; padding: var(--spacing-small); overflow-x: auto; font-size: 11px;"><code>use Crypt::CBC;
use Crypt::OpenSSL::AES;

sub _encrypt {
    my ($plaintext) = @_;
    return '' unless $plaintext;
    
    my $key = _get_encryption_key();
    
    my $cipher = Crypt::CBC->new(
        -key             => $key,
        -cipher          => 'Crypt::OpenSSL::AES',
        -header          => 'salt',
        -iterations      => 1,
        -randomiv        => 1
    );
    
    my $encrypted = $cipher->encrypt($plaintext);
    return 'ENC:' . encode_base64($encrypted, '');
}

sub _decrypt {
    my ($encrypted_data) = @_;
    return '' unless $encrypted_data;
    
    # Support legacy plaintext data
    return $encrypted_data unless $encrypted_data =~ /^ENC:/;
    
    $encrypted_data =~ s/^ENC://;
    my $encrypted_bytes = decode_base64($encrypted_data);
    my $key = _get_encryption_key();
    
    my $cipher = Crypt::CBC->new(
        -key    => $key,
        -cipher => 'Crypt::OpenSSL::AES',
        -header => 'salt',
    );
    
    return $cipher->decrypt($encrypted_bytes);
}
</code></pre>
            </div>

            <h4 style="color: #28a745; font-family: var(--header-font);">✅ Remediation Actions Completed</h4>
            <ol style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);">
                <li>✅ Added Crypt::CBC to cpanfile (line 67)</li>
                <li>✅ Added Crypt::OpenSSL::AES to cpanfile (line 68)</li>
                <li>✅ Added Crypt::Random to cpanfile (line 69)</li>
                <li>✅ Implemented AES-256-CBC encryption in ProxmoxCredentials.pm (lines 104-170)</li>
                <li>✅ Installed dependencies via carton install</li>
                <li>✅ Tested application startup - no compilation errors</li>
                <li>✅ Verified encryption/decryption functions operational</li>
                <li>✅ Committed: eede88cd - "Fix: Add missing Perl crypto dependencies to cpanfile"</li>
            </ol>

            <h4 style="color: #28a745; font-family: var(--header-font);">✅ Deployment Instructions</h4>
            <div style="background-color: white; padding: var(--spacing-small); border: 1px solid var(--border-color); margin: var(--spacing-small) 0; border-radius: 4px;">
                <pre style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: monospace; background-color: #f5f5f5; padding: var(--spacing-small); overflow-x: auto; font-size: 11px;"><code># 1. Install dependencies
cd Comserv
carton install

# 2. Generate encryption key (32 bytes for AES-256)
openssl rand -hex 16 > /tmp/proxmox_key.txt

# 3a. Option A: Use environment variable
export PROXMOX_ENCRYPTION_KEY=$(cat /tmp/proxmox_key.txt)

# 3b. Option B: Use file-based key (automatic)
mkdir -p config
openssl rand -base64 32 > config/.proxmox_encryption_key
chmod 0600 config/.proxmox_encryption_key

# 4. Start application
script/comserv_server.pl
</code></pre>
            </div>

            <h4 style="color: #28a745; font-family: var(--header-font);">✅ Verification Results</h4>
            <ul style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);">
                <li>✅ Application starts without "Can't locate Crypt::*" errors</li>
                <li>✅ ProxmoxCredentials.pm compiles successfully</li>
                <li>✅ Encryption/decryption functions tested and working</li>
                <li>✅ All crypto modules installed to local/lib/perl5/</li>
                <li>✅ Catalyst loads all models without errors</li>
            </ul>

            <p style="color: #28a745; font-family: var(--body-font); font-weight: bold; margin-top: var(--spacing-medium);">
                ✅ STATUS: FIXED, VERIFIED, AND READY FOR PRODUCTION DEPLOYMENT
            </p>
        </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Critical Issue 2: Database Passwords -->
    <div class="row">
        <div class="col-100" style="background-color: var(--light-color); border-left: 6px solid #dc3545; padding: var(--spacing-medium); margin: var(--spacing-medium) 0; border-radius: 4px;">
            <h3 style="color: #dc3545; font-family: var(--header-font);">2. Plaintext Database Passwords</h3>
            
            <p style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);"><strong>File:</strong> <code>db_config.template.json, ConfigDatabaseInit.pm:27-30</code> | <strong>CVSS:</strong> 9.3 | <strong>OWASP:</strong> A02:2021</p>

            <h4 style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font);">🚨 Problem</h4>
            <ul style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);">
                <li><strong>Hardcoded fallback password:</strong> <code>config_dev_password</code> in source code</li>
                <li><strong>No mandatory env vars:</strong> Defaults used if environment variables not set</li>
                <li><strong>Credentials in JSON:</strong> Template files expose credential structure</li>
                <li><strong>Multiple database compromise:</strong> Single breach = all databases compromised</li>
            </ul>

            <h4 style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font);">✅ Solution: Mandatory Environment Variables</h4>
            <div style="background-color: white; padding: var(--spacing-small); border: 1px solid var(--border-color); margin: var(--spacing-small) 0; border-radius: 4px;">
                <pre style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: monospace; background-color: #f5f5f5; padding: var(--spacing-small); overflow-x: auto;"><code># NO FALLBACKS - MANDATORY env vars
my $host = $ENV{CONFIG_DB_HOST} or die "CONFIG_DB_HOST not set";
my $port = $ENV{CONFIG_DB_PORT} or die "CONFIG_DB_PORT not set";
my $user = $ENV{CONFIG_DB_USER} or die "CONFIG_DB_USER not set";
my $pass = $ENV{CONFIG_DB_PASSWORD} or die "CONFIG_DB_PASSWORD not set";
my $db = $ENV{CONFIG_DB_NAME} or die "CONFIG_DB_NAME not set";
</code></pre>
            </div>

            <h4 style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font);">🔥 Immediate Actions</h4>
            <ol style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font); font-weight: bold;">
                <li>ROTATE ALL DATABASE CREDENTIALS IMMEDIATELY</li>
                <li>Check git history: <code>git log -p -- db_config.json | grep password</code></li>
                <li>Remove all environment variable fallbacks from code</li>
                <li>Use <code>.env.example</code> instead of JSON templates</li>
                <li>Require explicit environment variable setup before startup</li>
            </ol>
        </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Navigation Breakpoint -->
    <div class="row" style="margin: var(--spacing-medium) 0; padding: var(--spacing-small); background-color: var(--secondary-color); border-radius: 4px; text-align: center;">
        <div class="col-100">
            <p style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);">
                <a href="#critical-vulnerabilities" style="color: var(--link-color);">↑ Critical Issues</a> | 
                <a href="#high-severity" style="color: var(--link-color);">→ High Severity</a> | 
                <a href="/Documentation" style="color: var(--link-color);">Menu</a>
            </p>
        </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Critical Issue 3: Cookie Security -->
    <div class="row">
        <div class="col-100" style="background-color: var(--light-color); border-left: 6px solid #dc3545; padding: var(--spacing-medium); margin: var(--spacing-medium) 0; border-radius: 4px;">
            <h3 style="color: #dc3545; font-family: var(--header-font);">3. Cookie Security Misconfiguration</h3>
            
            <p style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);"><strong>File:</strong> <code>Comserv/lib/Comserv.pm:56-61</code> | <strong>CVSS:</strong> 8.8 | <strong>OWASP:</strong> A04:2021</p>

            <h4 style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font);">🚨 Problem</h4>
            <ul style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);">
                <li><strong><code>cookie_secure => 0</code>:</strong> Session cookies sent over HTTP unencrypted</li>
                <li><strong>Network interception possible:</strong> WiFi sniffing steals session tokens</li>
                <li><strong>Man-in-the-middle (MITM) attack:</strong> Attacker hijacks user session</li>
                <li><strong>Admin compromise:</strong> Stolen admin session = full system access</li>
                <li><strong>No CSRF protection:</strong> Missing SameSite cookie attribute</li>
            </ul>

            <h4 style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font);">✅ Solution: Secure Session Configuration</h4>
            <div style="background-color: white; padding: var(--spacing-small); border: 1px solid var(--border-color); margin: var(--spacing-small) 0; border-radius: 4px;">
                <pre style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: monospace; background-color: #f5f5f5; padding: var(--spacing-small); overflow-x: auto;"><code>'Plugin::Session' => {
    expires => 1800,              # Reduce to 30 minutes
    cookie_name => 'comserv_session',
    cookie_secure => 1,           # HTTPS ONLY
    cookie_httponly => 1,         # No JavaScript access
    cookie_samesite => 'Strict',  # CSRF protection
    cookie_domain => '.example.com',
},
</code></pre>
            </div>

            <h4 style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font);">🔥 Immediate Actions</h4>
            <ol style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font); font-weight: bold;">
                <li>ENFORCE HTTPS IN PRODUCTION (redirect HTTP → HTTPS)</li>
                <li>Update session configuration with code above</li>
                <li>Add HSTS header: <code>Strict-Transport-Security: max-age=31536000</code></li>
                <li>Revoke all existing sessions on deployment</li>
                <li>Monitor for session hijacking attempts in logs</li>
            </ol>
        </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Navigation Breakpoint -->
    <div class="row" style="margin: var(--spacing-medium) 0; padding: var(--spacing-small); background-color: var(--secondary-color); border-radius: 4px; text-align: center;">
        <div class="col-100">
            <p style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);">
                <a href="#critical-vulnerabilities" style="color: var(--link-color);">↑ Critical Issues</a> | 
                <a href="#high-severity" style="color: var(--link-color);">→ High Severity</a> | 
                <a href="/Documentation" style="color: var(--link-color);">Menu</a>
            </p>
        </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Critical Issue 4: Hardcoded User Bypass -->
    <div class="row">
        <div class="col-100" style="background-color: var(--light-color); border-left: 6px solid #dc3545; padding: var(--spacing-medium); margin: var(--spacing-medium) 0; border-radius: 4px;">
            <h3 style="color: #dc3545; font-family: var(--header-font);">4. Hardcoded Special User Bypass</h3>
            
            <p style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);"><strong>File:</strong> <code>Comserv/lib/Comserv/Util/AdminAuth.pm:56-62</code> | <strong>CVSS:</strong> 8.0 | <strong>OWASP:</strong> A01:2021</p>

            <h4 style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font);">🚨 Problem</h4>
            <ul style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);">
                <li><strong>Magic usernames:</strong> <code>'Shanta'</code> or <code>'ai_assistant'</code> bypass ALL authorization checks</li>
                <li><strong>Automatic admin access:</strong> No role verification required</li>
                <li><strong>Hardcoded in source:</strong> Persistent backdoor if code exposed</li>
                <li><strong>Account compromise = system compromise:</strong> Steal or create "Shanta" account = full access</li>
                <li><strong>No audit trail:</strong> Bypasses standard logging</li>
            </ul>

            <h4 style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font);">✅ Solution: Database-Only Role Checking</h4>
            <div style="background-color: white; padding: var(--spacing-small); border: 1px solid var(--border-color); margin: var(--spacing-small) 0; border-radius: 4px;">
                <pre style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: monospace; background-color: #f5f5f5; padding: var(--spacing-small); overflow-x: auto;"><code>sub check_admin_access {
    my ($self, $c, $action_name) = @_;
    
    # REMOVE all hardcoded special user checks
    # ONLY check database-stored roles
    
    my $user = $c->user or return 0;
    return 1 if $user->has_role('admin');
    return 0;
}
</code></pre>
            </div>

            <h4 style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font);">🔥 Immediate Actions</h4>
            <ol style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font); font-weight: bold;">
                <li>REMOVE ALL HARDCODED USERNAMES IMMEDIATELY from source code</li>
                <li>Search codebase: <code>grep -r "Shanta\|ai_assistant" Comserv/lib/</code></li>
                <li>Check git history for all uses: <code>git log -p | grep -i "Shanta\|ai_assistant"</code></li>
                <li>Force password reset for "Shanta" and "ai_assistant" accounts</li>
                <li>Audit access logs for unauthorized use of these accounts</li>
                <li>Implement proper RBAC from database only</li>
            </ol>
        </div>
    </div>

    <!-- HIGH SEVERITY SECTION -->
    <div class="row" style="margin-top: var(--spacing-large);">
        <div class="col-100">
            <h2 id="high-severity" style="color: #ff8c42; font-family: var(--header-font);">🟠 HIGH SEVERITY VULNERABILITIES</h2>
            <p style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);">Address within 1-2 weeks. Timeline is flexible but urgent before full production.</p>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="row">
        <div class="col-100" style="background-color: var(--light-color); border-left: 6px solid #ff8c42; padding: var(--spacing-medium); margin: var(--spacing-medium) 0; border-radius: 4px;">
            <h3 style="color: #ff8c42; font-family: var(--header-font);">1. Missing CSRF Token Protection</h3>
            <p style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);"><strong>CVSS:</strong> 8.1 | <strong>Timeline:</strong> 1-2 weeks</p>
            <p style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);"><strong>Issue:</strong> All POST/DELETE/PUT operations lack CSRF token validation. Attacker can forge requests on behalf of authenticated users.</p>
            <h4 style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font);">Action Items:</h4>
            <ul style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);">
                <li>Generate CSRF token on every request in session</li>
                <li>Add hidden field to all forms with token value</li>
                <li>Validate token on all state-changing operations</li>
                <li>Use Catalyst::Plugin::CSRF or similar</li>
                <li>Combine with SameSite cookies from Critical Issue #3</li>
            </ul>
        </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Navigation Breakpoint -->
